Islamabad denied violating the ceasefire in Kashmir, a region that has sparked wars between India and Pakistan.
Indian police reported mortar fire from Pakistan into India's Durga Post area.
The ceasefire, in place since 2003, faces scrutiny as military commanders discuss violations.
A bus service between Indian and Pakistan zones of Kashmir is set to resume, symbolizing progress in peace talks.
Emotional reunions across the Neelum River mark a hopeful turn in relations.
Talks on Kashmir's future are imminent, with both countries showing willingness to engage in dialogue for a lasting solution.
